{"type":"message","id":"8eb6c209","parentId":"578577df","timestamp":"2026-03-29T03:16:27.665Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sravya is happy with the birthday wishes. Simple warm close.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Anytime @Sravya! 🎂 Hope they love it! Happy birthday to the lucky person 🎉⚡"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":903,"output":56,"cacheRead":59584,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60543,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774754184084}}
{"type":"message","id":"7aba46f7","parentId":"8eb6c209","timestamp":"2026-03-29T03:46:29.951Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"168\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-29 03:46 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"history_count\": 2\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\"\n}\n```\n\nChat history since last reply (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Nemesis (@nemesis0008) id:7924461837\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1774755520000,\n    \"body\": \"who?\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \". id:1880938940\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1774755598000,\n    \"body\": \"Prasanna’s kid\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\n@Nexa_autobot \nAs today is Sunday tell nice dish so i can prepare\nNote: Only veg recipes"}],"timestamp":1774755989946}}
{"type":"message","id":"f51240c2","parentId":"7aba46f7","timestamp":"2026-03-29T03:46:40.888Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sravya wants a nice vegetarian recipe for Sunday. Let me suggest a good dish.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Sunday cooking time @Sravya! Here are some yummy veg dishes 👇\n\n**🏆 My Top Pick: Paneer Butter Masala** 🧡\n\nRich, creamy, and restaurant-quality at home!\n\n**Ingredients:**\n• Paneer — 250g (cubed)\n• Tomatoes — 4 large (pureed)\n• Onion — 2 (finely chopped)\n• Butter — 3 tbsp\n• Cream — 4 tbsp\n• Ginger-garlic paste — 1 tbsp\n• Kashmiri red chilli powder — 1 tsp\n• Garam masala — 1 tsp\n• Kasuri methi — 1 tsp\n• Sugar — 1 tsp\n• Salt to taste\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Heat butter, sauté onions till golden\n2. Add ginger-garlic paste, cook 2 mins\n3. Add tomato puree, cook till oil separates (~10 min)\n4. Add chilli powder, garam masala, sugar, salt\n5. Add cream, mix well\n6. Add paneer cubes, simmer 5 mins\n7. Crush kasuri methi on top\n8. Serve with butter naan or jeera rice 🍚\n\n**Other Sunday Special Ideas:**\n• 🍛 **Veg Biryani** — if you want something filling\n• 🥘 **Chole Bhature** — classic Sunday brunch vibes\n• 🍜 **Dal Makhani** — slow cooked, heavenly\n• 🫓 **Stuffed Paratha + Curd** — easy & satisfying\n\nWant me to share a detailed recipe for any of these @Sravya? Happy cooking! 👩‍🍳⚡"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":57806,"output":397,"cacheRead":3072,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61275,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774755989950}}
{"type":"message","id":"ace5c9c3","parentId":"f51240c2","timestamp":"2026-03-29T03:48:13.908Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"170\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"169\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-29 03:48 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Sunday cooking time @Sravya! Here are some yummy veg dishes 👇\\n\\n🏆 My Top Pick: Paneer Butter Masala 🧡\\n\\nRich, creamy, and restaurant-quality at home!\\n\\nIngredients:\\n• Paneer — 250g (cubed)\\n• Tomatoes — 4 large (pureed)\\n• Onion — 2 (finely chopped)\\n• Butter — 3 tbsp\\n• Cream — 4 tbsp\\n• Ginger-garlic paste — 1 tbsp\\n• Kashmiri red chilli powder — 1 tsp\\n• Garam masala — 1 tsp\\n• Kasuri methi — 1 tsp\\n• Sugar — 1 tsp\\n• Salt to taste\\n\\nSteps:\\n\\n1. Heat butter, sauté onions till golden\\n2. Add ginger-garlic paste, cook 2 mins\\n3. Add tomato puree, cook till oil separates (~10 min)\\n4. Add chilli powder, garam masala, sugar, salt\\n5. Add cream, mix well\\n6. Add paneer cubes, simmer 5 mins\\n7. Crush kasuri methi on top\\n8. Serve with butter naan or jeera rice 🍚\\n\\nOther Sunday Special Ideas:\\n• 🍛 Veg Biryani — if you want something filling\\n• 🥘 Chole Bhature — classic Sunday brunch vibes\\n• 🍜 Dal Makhani — slow cooked, heavenly\\n• 🫓 Stuffed Paratha + Curd — easy & satisfying\\n\\nWant me to share a detailed recipe for any of these @Sravya? Happy cooking! 👩‍🍳⚡\"\n}\n```\n\nGo with some south Indian traditional and old dishes( telugu dishes)"}],"timestamp":1774756093902}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c53977c","parentId":"ace5c9c3","timestamp":"2026-03-29T03:48:23.458Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sravya wants traditional Telugu/South Indian dishes. Let me give her some authentic Telugu vegetarian recipes.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Now we're talking @Sravya! Here are some traditional Telugu veg dishes 👇\n\n**🏆 Top Pick: Pesarattu + Upma** 🟢\nThe OG Telugu breakfast/lunch combo!\n\n**Pesarattu (Green Moong Dal Dosa):**\n• Green moong dal — 1 cup (soaked 6-8 hrs)\n• Rice — 2 tbsp\n• Green chilli — 3\n• Ginger — 1 inch\n• Cumin — 1 tsp\n• Salt to taste\n• Oil for cooking\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Grind moong dal, rice, chilli, ginger, cumin to smooth batter\n2. Add salt, mix well (slightly thick batter)\n3. Heat tawa, spread batter like dosa\n4. Drizzle oil, cook both sides till crispy\n5. Serve with upma + ginger chutney 🔥\n\n---\n\n**🍛 Other Telugu Classics:**\n\n**Gutti Vankaya Kura** 🍆\nStuffed brinjal curry — the queen of Telugu cuisine!\n• Small brinjals stuffed with peanut-sesame-coconut masala\n• Rich, spicy, absolutely divine\n\n**Pappu Charu** 🍲\nTelugu-style dal with a tangy twist\n• Toor dal + tomatoes + tamarind + light spices\n• Comfort food at its finest\n\n**Pulihora** 🍛\nTamarind rice — temple prasadam vibes\n• Tangy, spicy, crunchy peanuts\n• Every Telugu person's soul food\n\n**Dondakaya Fry** 🥒\nIvy gourd stir fry — crispy and addictive\n• Sliced ivy gourd + red chilli + curry leaves\n• Best side dish ever\n\n**Pesarapappu Payasam** 🍮\nMoong dal kheer — perfect dessert\n• Sweet, creamy, cardamom flavored\n\nWant the full recipe for any of these @Sravya? 👩‍🍳⚡"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":1002,"output":482,"cacheRead":60864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62348,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774756093907}}
{"type":"message","id":"20fc737d","parentId":"9c53977c","timestamp":"2026-03-29T03:50:18.407Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"172\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"171\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-29 03:50 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Now we're talking @Sravya! Here are some traditional Telugu veg dishes 👇\\n\\n🏆 Top Pick: Pesarattu + Upma 🟢\\nThe OG Telugu breakfast/lunch combo!\\n\\nPesarattu (Green Moong Dal Dosa):\\n• Green moong dal — 1 cup (soaked 6-8 hrs)\\n• Rice — 2 tbsp\\n• Green chilli — 3\\n• Ginger — 1 inch\\n• Cumin — 1 tsp\\n• Salt to taste\\n• Oil for cooking\\n\\nSteps:\\n\\n1. Grind moong dal, rice, chilli, ginger, cumin to smooth batter\\n2. Add salt, mix well (slightly thick batter)\\n3. Heat tawa, spread batter like dosa\\n4. Drizzle oil, cook both sides till crispy\\n5. Serve with upma + ginger chutney 🔥\\n\\n───\\n\\n🍛 Other Telugu Classics:\\n\\nGutti Vankaya Kura 🍆\\nStuffed brinjal curry — the queen of Telugu cuisine!\\n• Small brinjals stuffed with peanut-sesame-coconut masala\\n• Rich, spicy, absolutely divine\\n\\nPappu Charu 🍲\\nTelugu-style dal with a tangy twist\\n• Toor dal + tomatoes + tamarind + light spices\\n• Comfort food at its finest\\n\\nPulihora 🍛\\nTamarind rice — temple prasadam vibes\\n• Tangy, spicy, crunchy peanuts\\n• Every Telugu person's soul food\\n\\nDondakaya Fry 🥒\\nIvy gourd stir fry — crispy and addictive\\n• Sliced ivy gourd + red chilli + curry leaves\\n• Best side dish ever\\n\\nPesarapappu Payasam 🍮\\nMoong dal kheer — perfect dessert\\n• Sweet, creamy, cardamom flavored\\n\\nWant the full recipe for any of these @Sravya? 👩‍🍳⚡\"\n}\n```\n\nCan u give me the recipe of oats bismilla bath or smg related to oats"}],"timestamp":1774756218395}}
{"type":"message","id":"20b22b2f","parentId":"20fc737d","timestamp":"2026-03-29T03:50:29.639Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sravya is asking about \"oats bismilla bath\" - she probably means \"Oats Bisi Bele Bath\" which is a South Indian dish. Bisi Bele Bath is a traditional Karnataka dish but popular across South India. Let me give her a recipe for Oats Bisi Bele Bath, which is a healthier twist on the classic.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Oh nice choice @Sravya! You mean **Oats Bisi Bele Bath** — the healthy twist on the classic! Here you go 👇\n\n**🍛 Oats Bisi Bele Bath** 🥣\n\nA healthier version of the iconic South Indian one-pot meal!\n\n**Ingredients:**\n• Oats — 1 cup (roasted lightly)\n• Toor dal — ½ cup (cooked)\n• Tamarind paste — 1 tbsp\n• Turmeric — ½ tsp\n• Mixed vegetables — 1 cup (carrot, beans, peas, potato)\n• Water — 3 cups\n• Salt to taste\n• Ghee — 2 tbsp\n\n**For the Masala Paste:**\n• Coconut — 2 tbsp\n• Red chillies — 3-4\n• Coriander seeds — 1 tbsp\n• Chana dal — 1 tsp\n• Urad dal — 1 tsp\n• Cinnamon — 1 small stick\n• Cloves — 3\n• Cardamom — 1\n• Poppy seeds — 1 tsp (optional)\n\n**For Tempering:**\n• Ghee — 1 tbsp\n• Mustard seeds — 1 tsp\n• Curry leaves — 10\n• Cashews — 8-10\n• Dry red chilli — 1\n\n**Steps:**\n1. Roast masala ingredients in little oil, grind to smooth paste\n2. Cook vegetables in water with turmeric till soft\n3. Add cooked dal, tamarind paste, masala paste, salt\n4. Boil for 5 mins\n5. Add roasted oats, stir well\n6. Cook 3-4 mins till oats absorb the flavors\n7. Add ghee, mix\n8. Temper with mustard, curry leaves, cashews, red chilli\n9. Pour tempering on top\n10. Serve hot with boondi or chips! 🔥\n\n**💡 Tips:**\n• Don't overcook oats — they get mushy fast\n• Extra ghee = extra happiness 🧈\n• Add peanuts for crunch\n• Papad on the side is a must!\n\nEnjoy your Sunday cooking @Sravya! 👩‍🍳⚡"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":1199,"output":619,"cacheRead":61824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63642,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774756218406}}
